## Final Checklist — Before Marking Implementation Complete

```
□ All trigger conditions checked (model / service / serializer / view / util / signal)
□ Test file exists at the mirrored path with correct test_ prefix
□ Existing fixtures reused from conftest.py — no duplicates created
□ Happy path covered
□ Edge cases covered
□ Failure cases covered
□ Permission and authorization scenarios covered
□ All new branches and conditionals have explicit test coverage
□ Parametrize used where multiple similar inputs are tested
□ No hardcoded values — factories used throughout
□ All tests are isolated and deterministic
□ No unnecessary DB hits — mocks used for external side effects
□ Coverage mentally verified: every new line and branch is exercised
□ Audit summary from django-audit-loop updated to include test status
```

> ✅ Implementation is only **finalized** when every item above is checked.  
> ❌ Code without tests is **not complete** — it is a draft.
